The '''Nishanvali/Nishanvala Misl''' was founded by the sardar jai singh ji and its founder was [[jai singh ji]].


The Nishanavali misl, kept as a reserve force at Amritsar, used to act as standard-bearers of the Khalsa army "Dal Khalsa". Hence the name (Nishan = flag or standard; vali/vala= owning or unfurling) means this misl carry the Nishan Sahib, the Sikh Flag in the battle. 
[[This misl has two 12 feet long Naishan sabih which they used to carry wars]] the flags are still there but they have been kept by family there of this misl 
This Sikh Misl had a strength of 2000 regular horsemen and covered the areas of [[Rupnagar district|Roopnagar]], [[Ambala]] and [[Shahabad Markanda|Shahbad Markanda.]]

