[[Category:Sociology of religion]]

In the [[Tenrikyo]] religion, the '''Shinbashira''' (真柱 "central pillar") refers to the "administrative and spiritual leader" of [[Tenrikyo Church Headquarters]].<ref>[http://www.tenrikyo.or.jp/en/newsletter/html/tt5/shinbashira.html "Central Pillar (''Shinbashira'')" by Yoshikazu Fukaya]</ref> The ''Constitution of Tenrikyo'' defines the position as "the one who governs Tenrikyo."<ref>''Constitution of Tenrikyo'', Article 8.</ref>

The fourth and current Shinbashira is Nakayama Zenji (中山善司), who has held the office since April 26, 1998.

